<br>
As I watch, with my gut renched, I realize how much *less risk* and *quick* this goes without tanks (available to us) taking hits from the chosen mobs and mini bosses. Surely my friend will get popped every now and again, but she is often up and running with full mana 0.5 seconds after a rez.<br>
<br>
I could choose to group with other people I know and care about less, but sitting on my butt chatting would gain me exp faster... I choose to chat from my alt. I adore my enchanter friend to bits, but it makes me want to vomit after all the hard work I have put in thus far and the work I have yet to do to reach my full potential.<br>
<br>
For my personal benefit they have tried to accomplish this the traditional way. Even with a knight, there are too many variables that can cause failure. I can't bring myself to be upset with my friend because she's been handed these tools. I dare not speak too loudly for fear of initiating the nerf bat. I hope she never finds this post. I have a 58 druid I could get tier3 access, but then I would just give into my beliefs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">I can't think of a single way for SOE to invalidate my personal efforts more.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <br>
