<br>
First of all on the pet taunt issue. If any melee is in range the mob will turn on them. VI changed that code when the AOW was first killed since they were using pets to tank him. So your pet taunts till a PC is in range.<br>
<br>
We use charm pets in fights often but not to tank. Charmed pets just add DPS for our raids which is what they were meant to do. Any RAID that uses pets to tank is just cheesy. Pet tanking means getting hit, and that can only happen if the pet is alone on the mob. So some people actually let a pet kill when they have a raid present? I can see a solo druid or chanter using one, or even a small xp group maybe but a raid? Is your guild so weak you cant tank a Storms named? lol<br>
<br>
