<br>
An enchanter that has never received a drop from a single raid encounter will be &gt; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Overlord</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Overlord</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a clown warrior next to the pet of an enchanter, one that doesn't require loot nor exp nor taunt consideration.<br>
<br>
No matter your level, how many aa, or how many months of raid upgrades, you will *never* do more dps and or tank better than a CoD charmed NPC selected from tier1 and up. *Ever*<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">This isn't ok. Normal and extended class abilities should not be better than the combined best of another class which includes the best armor drops at the expense of 40+ people's weekends and weekday evenings.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
There are many tactics that exclude a pc tanking, but they are clumsy, often stressful, and can allow close quarter melee to participate. This one isn't and doesn't. It's godly efficient, easy to understand, and near risk free if the participants are doing it correctly and out of melee range.<br>
<br>
Now, charm as an auxilliary source of dps on raids or otherwise is fine by me. For my friend alone, I hope they don't nerf it, but dear god I just have to express myself.<br>
